==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thoroughfare
<hw>Thor"ough*fare`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧urhfaru</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A passage through; a
passage from one street or opening to another; an unobstructed way open
to the public; a public road; hence, a frequented street.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A large and splendid <qex>thoroughfare</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A passing or going through; passage.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Made] Hell and this world -- one realm, one continent⟦br⟧
Of easy <qex>thoroughfare</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thoroughgoing</ent>⟦br⟧
